# Always: Memory Bank Paths

## Canonical paths

- `memory-bank/tasks.md` — source of truth for active task.
- `memory-bank/activeContext.md` — current focus and assumptions.
- `memory-bank/progress.md` — progress log.
- `memory-bank/projectbrief.md` — stable project brief.
- `memory-bank/productContext.md` — business context.
- `memory-bank/systemPatterns.md` — architecture patterns.
- `memory-bank/techContext.md` — tooling/platform context.
- `memory-bank/creative/` — creative/architecture decisions.
- `memory-bank/reflection/` — lessons and error reflections.
- `memory-bank/archive/` — completed tasks.

## Rules

- Do not create `tasks.md` outside `memory-bank/`.
- Do not put transient logs into Memory Bank; summarize only.
- Do not store secrets or passwords in Memory Bank.
- For non-trivial tasks, update `tasks.md` and `progress.md`.
- For architecture choices, write `memory-bank/creative/creative-YYYY-MM-DD-<topic>.md`.
- For completed tasks, archive instead of leaving context scattered in chat.
